// ============================================================
// OBLIVIOUS AI EA - Expert Advisor for MetaTrader 4
// Version: 3.00  |  Refactored: 2026-03-30
// Last full audit: 2026-05-24 — ALL 8 priority upgrades verified PRESENT.
//   P1 OBL_Filter* soften + helpers .......... PRESENT (line 37723+, 36971+)
//   P2 SMC PRO (BOS+CHoCH+disp+inducement) ... PRESENT (OBL_FilterSMC_OK 37796)
//   P3 ICT PRO (KZ+sweep+OTE+Judas) .......... PRESENT (OBL_FilterICT_OK 37839)
//   P4 BREAKOUT PRO (compress+disp+failBO) ... PRESENT (OBL_FilterBreakout_OK 37739)
//   P5 BE vs TPSL conflict .................. RESOLVED (ManageBreakEven 20669/20673)
//   P6 ClusterMoney post-BE only ............. PRESENT (ClusterMoney_OnTick 22550)
//   P7 MTF mini-multipliers .................. PRESENT (OBL_AdaptiveLevels 36770)
//   P8 FVG bias + HTF gate ................... PRESENT (Strategy_FVG_Logic_v2 47968)
// Lifecycle ITER 19 (11 stati setup) ......... PRESENT (OBL_LifecycleTick 37283)
// LIVE state machine UNARMED→PROT→BE→TRAIL .. PRESENT (TPSLManager_OnTick 22869)
// Panels (Dyn/Smart/SmartLog/Trigger) ........ TO SPEC (DynPanel_Update 38546+)
// Support engines hardgate (news/cancel only) PRESENT (SupportEngines_HardGate 28992)
// Architecture: 3-Level (Owner Strategies / Indicator Modules / Pattern Support)
//
// LEVEL 1 - OWNER STRATEGIES (6 canonical, own all trades):
//   Predicted, Grid, Breakout, FVG, SMC, ICT, Reverse (7 strategies)
//
// LEVEL 2 - INDICATOR ENGINE + FILTER ENGINE (always-on, internal, non-owner):
//   Indicator Engine: RSI, MACD, ADX, Bollinger, Stochastic, EMA, SMA, ATR + 80+ more
//                     -> g_ind_consensus / g_ind_*_score via DispatchIndicatorStrategies()
//   Filter Engine:    volatility regime, session quality, spread, structure, exhaustion
//                     -> g_filter_confidence / g_filter_support via UpdateFilterEngine()
//   Both run on every tick. They produce bias / confidence / quality / penalty
//   only — NEVER hard-block trades. The only user-tunable knobs are policy
//   thresholds (IndicatorsConfidence / FiltersConfidence / PatternsConfidence /
//   HybridMinConfidence).
//   Per-indicator on/off toggles have been removed from inputs and converted
//   to internal `const bool` symbols (see "INDICATOR ENGINE + FILTER ENGINE"
//   block in SECTION 03), so the engines are permanently active like Pattern.
//
// LEVEL 2.5 - HYBRID ENGINE (always-on, internal, non-owner, soft):
//   Multi-step ICT/SMC model classifier: 4 reversal models (Sweep+MSS+FVG,
//   Breaker+OTE, Unicorn, Judas+FVG), 4 continuation models (OB+FVG conf.,
//   OB-Mitigation+OTE, Liquidity+Breaker+FVG, AMD expansion) and 2 advanced
//   models (SMT+MSS+FVG when correlation feed available; Macro-Time+Liq+FVG).
//   Outputs g_hyb_* (confidence/bias/quality/penalty/entry zone/liq target/
//   freshness/invalidation/hold/cancel + model id and class) consumed via
//   Hybrid_RefineConfidence / Hybrid_RefineBias / Hybrid_QualityFor /
//   Hybrid_ShouldDiscourage by the SIX non-Predicted owners (Breakout, FVG,
//   Grid, SMC, ICT, Reverse). Predicted is intentionally excluded from
//   Hybrid as primary engine; at most it reads g_hyb_* as context.
//
// LEVEL 3 - PATTERN ENGINE (always active, non-owner, context only):
//   Engulfing, Hammer, Doji, PinBar, MorningStar, TurtleSoup, Fakey,
//   Quasimodo, 2B Reversal, Spring/Upthrust, Engulfing+MACD trend
//   confluence, harami / inside-bar / 3-bar / order-block / structure-break
//   / liquidity-grab / FVG continuation, and more.
//   All contribute to g_pat_consensus / g_pat_direction_support via
//   DispatchPatternStrategies(). No pattern detector opens trades on its
//   own and no pattern detector is exposed as a separate user-facing module.
//
// HARD vs SOFT GATES:
//   Hard gates (block trade): risk caps, lot validity, license/SecureBoot,
//     spread hard cap (MaxSpreadPoints), news high-impact windows, schedule
//     windows, missing essential data.
//   Soft engines (no direct block): Indicator / Filter / Pattern engines.
//     They lower confidence, penalize ranking, discourage add-ons, downgrade
//     setup quality — but never veto a trade by themselves.
//
// DISPATCH CHAIN:
//   OnTick -> Orchestrator_OnTick -> {
//     DispatchIndicatorStrategies  (Level 2:   Indicator Engine context)
//     UpdateFilterEngine           (Level 2:   Filter    Engine context)
//     DispatchPatternStrategies    (Level 3:   Pattern   Engine context  non-owner)
//     DispatchAIStrategy           (Level 2:   AI context support)
//     UpdateHybridEngine           (Level 2.5: Hybrid    Engine context  non-owner,
//                                              NOT applied to Predicted as primary)
//     DispatchPredictedStrategy    (Level 1:   Predicted strategy owner)
//     FVG_Logic                    (Level 1:   FVG       strategy owner)
//     Strategy_SMC_Logic           (Level 1:   SMC       strategy owner)
//     Strategy_ICT_Logic           (Level 1:   ICT       strategy owner)
//     ExecuteStrategies            (Level 1:   Grid + Breakout + Reverse owners)
//   }
//
// SECTIONS:
//   01: Header / #property / #import / kernel32
//   02: #define / constants / macros / config
//   03: Input / user parameters
//   04: Enum / struct / types
//   05: Globals / state / ownership / bridge buffers
//   06: Forward declarations
//   07: Utility / logging / math / time / string / price
//   08: Bridge kernel32 / news / AI pipe / parsing / polling
//   09: State / persistence / KPI / performance / adaptive logic
//   10: Dashboard / UI / drawing / toggles
//   11: Indicators raw / Is* / Get* / candle helpers
//   12: Indicator signal + confidence
//   13: Filters raw / helpers / filter score
//   14: Filter confidence / combined filter
//   15: Patterns raw / FVG / SMC / ICT / liquidity / structure
//   16: Pattern signal + confidence / combined pattern
//   17: Risk / exposure / lot sizing / challenge / drawdown
//   18: Execution / order / position management
//   19: TP-SL / trailing / breakeven / profit guards / overlays
//   20: Strategy helpers / orchestrator / dispatchers
//   21: Strategy_<Indicator>_Logic (indicator context producers)
//   25: Indicator enabled flags
//   26: Late global declarations
//   27: Recovered helpers (utility, session, pattern)
//   28: Indicator strategy minimal implementations
//   29: Global helpers and pattern utilities
//   30: Globals, indicator flags, candlestick helpers
// ============================================================

// SECTION 01: HEADER / #PROPERTY / #IMPORT / KERNEL32

#property copyright "OBLIVIOUS AI EA"
#property version "3.0"
#property strict

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Forward macro defs: MQL4 preprocessor is single-pass; these
// macros are referenced before their original definition mid-file.
// Promoted here with #ifndef so the original later #defines stay
// no-op (no "macro redefined" warning).
// ----------------------------------------------------------------
#ifndef PENDING_LIFECYCLE_LOG
#define PENDING_LIFECYCLE_LOG  true
#endif
